  m_Name: Hermit Crab
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FishData
  <fishName>k__BackingField: hermit crab
  <fishFact>k__BackingField: "Unlike most crustaceans, hermit crabs are born without
    a hard shell of their own, so they move into empty shells left behind by snails
    \u2014 and upgrade to a bigger one as they grow. They've been spotted forming
    organized \"vacancy chains,\" where a group of crabs lines up by size and passes
    their old shells down the line so everyone gets a better fit! "
